What kind of matrix traversal is <image 1>?

A. Normal traversal of the matrix.
B. Row-wise traversal of the matrix.
C. Column-wise traversal of the matrix.
D. spiral traversal of the matrix.

The image shows a matrix traversal where the elements are visited in a spiral pattern, starting from the top left corner and moving clockwise around the boundary of the matrix. This type of traversal is known as a spiral traversal.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

D. Spiral traversal of the matrix.
